main event: Observers in East Prairie, Missouri reported multiple unidentified flying objects on several occasions in April and May of 1953.
interesting points: The first report involved two witnesses seeing three objects moving in a straight line at high altitude., One object was described as round with a diameter of about 6-7 feet and stationary during the observation., On another occasion, two unidentified objects were observed moving at speeds estimated between 1000 and 1500 mph., The observers noted that the objects did not leave any exhaust trails., The reports indicate uncertainty about the nature and origin of the objects, with suggestions they were beyond current knowledge of flight.
witness description: Local residents and observers, including a retired church member.
